# FreePads Project Structure Guide

This is a React 19 + Vite 7 + Tailwind CSS v4 project for building a pads application.

## Key Files and Structure

- **Entry Point**: [src/main.jsx](mdc:src/main.jsx) - Main application entry point
- **Main Component**: [src/App.jsx](mdc:src/App.jsx) - Root React component
- **Build Config**: [vite.config.js](mdc:vite.config.js) - Vite configuration
- **CSS Framework**: [tailwind.config.js](mdc:tailwind.config.js) - Tailwind CSS v4 configuration
- **Linting**: [eslint.config.js](mdc:eslint.config.js) - ESLint configuration
- **Dependencies**: [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Project dependencies and scripts

## Project Conventions

- Use React 19 features and hooks
- Follow ESLint rules defined in [eslint.config.js](mdc:eslint.config.js)
- Use Tailwind CSS v4 for styling (utility-first approach)
- All source code is in the `src/` directory
- Use ES modules (import/export syntax)
- Follow the existing file structure and naming conventions